436fa2c3-6fd5-4a9d-9f93-ae7f748867bf	18b3d5ac-a0e1-4b86-b1e9-1fe6807ae0a4	Wirecard	adverse_media	0.95	{18b3d5ac-a0e1-4b86-b1e9-1fe6807ae0a4}	In June 2020, Wirecard's auditors uncovered that EUR 1.9 billion supposedly held in two Philippine bank accounts (BDO and BPI) had never existed. Both banks confirmed that documents bearing their letterheads were fabrications. This signals a massive accounting fraud scheme where material assets were fictitiously reported, indicating serious misconduct and fraudulent financial reporting at the entity level.	Escalate immediately for enhanced due diligence review. Verify current regulatory status and sanctions/enforcement actions against Wirecard and its leadership. Review account activity and transaction history for any suspicious patterns. Consider account termination if Wirecard remains a customer, or heightened monitoring if relationship has already been severed. Cross-reference with global enforcement databases (OFAC, EU, etc.) for any related penalties or asset freezes.	proposed	claude-haiku-4-5	1551	314	0.003121	2026-06-20 00:14:14.711+00
10a653da-cba9-4892-b52e-31cf156601f2	ebdc7fb6-fad4-4f1d-9209-d16eb79d8065	Wirecard	adverse_media	0.85	{ebdc7fb6-fad4-4f1d-9209-d16eb79d8065}	The Bloomberg article title explicitly references Wirecard within the context of a "global payments scandal." The reference to Germany being "scarred by Wirecard" indicates the entity has a history of major misconduct. While the snippet does not provide granular detail on the current nature or timing of the scandal referenced, the headline clearly associates Wirecard with scandal and reputational damage. This represents ongoing adverse media coverage linking the entity to fraudulent or improper financial activity.	Conduct a detailed review of the full Bloomberg article to determine: (1) whether this references the historical 2020 Wirecard collapse/fraud or new allegations; (2) Wirecard's current operational status and any active business relationships; (3) whether any related parties or successor entities warrant added scrutiny. If Wirecard remains an active customer, escalate for immediate KYC/compliance review given fraud history.	proposed	claude-haiku-4-5	1486	320	0.003086	2026-06-20 00:14:18.41+00
7df899df-78c0-4f71-8559-66519edbd934	6bfa0fb2-e067-4603-819d-17e2a0b1d6b1	Wirecard	adverse_media	0.85	{6bfa0fb2-e067-4603-819d-17e2a0b1d6b1}	The signal reports on Wirecard's Singapore whistleblower and references evidence that "Munich tried to bury," indicating serious allegations of wrongdoing and potential cover-up attempts. This represents significant adverse media coverage directly tied to Wirecard's past fraudulent accounting scandal, reinforcing reputational risk and suggesting ongoing revelations about the company's misconduct and attempts to suppress evidence.	Review full article to assess whether entity remains in active enforcement or legal proceedings. Cross-reference with existing Wirecard compliance file given the company's well-documented 2020 accounting fraud. Consider whether ongoing revelations about the scandal present renewed reputational or legal risk to the institution if the entity is an existing client.	confirmed	claude-haiku-4-5	1524	283	0.002939	2026-06-20 00:14:11.332+00
f58a08fc-c35b-43e6-b976-c9d01db5279e	2f2b885c-784b-4c36-aa4e-27a2197b5ff7	Wirecard	financial_distress	0.92	{2f2b885c-784b-4c36-aa4e-27a2197b5ff7}	The signal reports that Wirecard shareholders will receive no money from the insolvency estate, as stated by RÖDL (a restructuring and insolvency advisory firm). This is a direct confirmation of completed insolvency proceedings. Wirecard's insolvency is well-documented as a major financial collapse; this article reflects the final outcome where the company's estate has insufficient assets to satisfy shareholder claims, indicating severe and irreversible financial distress.	Verify Wirecard's current insolvency status and update KYC records if the entity is still held as a customer or counterparty. Ensure any existing exposure is flagged for immediate review and close-out. Flag for monitoring of any related entities or shell companies that may attempt to operate under similar branding.	proposed	claude-haiku-4-5	1480	300	0.00298	2026-06-20 00:14:42.69+00
63973ff9-47e3-40c4-a4ec-b287ac85f97d	8a0a181e-ed77-4587-8b1d-132a09dbe470	Wirecard	adverse_media	0.45	{8a0a181e-ed77-4587-8b1d-132a09dbe470}	Signal reports on the Wirecard scandal and a Singapore firm (oCap Management) losing a bid to access frozen funds related to lawsuits. While this references the widely-known Wirecard accounting fraud scandal, the article itself concerns a subsidiary or related entity (oCap Management) and a civil litigation outcome regarding fund access, rather than direct wrongdoing by the primary entity. The reputational connection to Wirecard is indirect and the news is primarily about a court decision on frozen assets, not new misconduct allegations.	Verify whether oCap Management or the entity under review has direct involvement in the Wirecard scandal beyond asset recovery proceedings. If the entity is oCap Management itself or a Wirecard subsidiary, escalate for further due diligence. If it is merely a claimant or peripheral party in legacy Wirecard litigation, consider this routine adverse media with limited current risk and recommend closing with documentation.	proposed	claude-haiku-4-5	1506	328	0.003146	2026-06-20 00:14:46.36+00
530c1d0f-c02e-41a3-b13c-93a094da63bc	32356ee3-4ff4-4de9-9073-fa9fa80c7b32	Wirecard	adverse_media	0.75	{32356ee3-4ff4-4de9-9073-fa9fa80c7b32}	News report indicates Singapore sentencing of businessmen for falsifying Wirecard documents. This represents ongoing legal consequences and reputational damage related to Wirecard's well-documented fraud scandal. The report documents criminal prosecution linked to document falsification in connection with Wirecard, reinforcing the entity's association with fraud and misconduct that poses reputational risk.	Review if Wirecard or related entities remain subject to monitoring obligations. Cross-reference sentencing details with any ongoing regulatory actions or sanctions. Consider escalation if Wirecard entity is an existing customer or counterparty. Update risk profile based on jurisdictional enforcement actions.	proposed	claude-haiku-4-5	1477	264	0.002797	2026-06-20 00:14:49.304+00
